**Claim + frontier map (goal session 2026-06-10, afternoon lane).** Working the last #327 residual now: `FinalSumcheckStepLogicCompleteResidual` (ReductionLogic.lean:1694). Verified on current main: `lake build ArkLib.ProofSystem.Binius.BinaryBasefold.ReductionLogic` is green at `a075a1b66`, and ALL machinery for the discharge now exists in-tree:

- `strictOracleFoldingConsistency_last_getLastOracle_eq_prefixFold` (Reconstruct/FinalOracleBridge.lean:40) — getLastOracle = prefix fold through level ℓ−ϑ;
- `iterated_fold_transitivity` + `_castfree` (Prelude.lean:1124/1226) — fold composition;
- `getFoldingChallenges_append_finalBlock` (Basic.lean:1149) — prefix ++ final-ϑ block = foldOrderChallenges;
- `getMidCodewords_last_apply_eq_eval` (Reconstruct/IteratedFoldToLevel.lean:75) — full fold = t(statement challenges);
- `finalSumcheckStep_{verifierCheck_passed, final_codeword_eq_eval, strictOracleFoldingConsistency_out}` (ReductionLogic.lean:1251/1237/1274).

The single missing weld is the final-constant consistency: `iterated_fold (getLastOracle oStmtIn) (final ϑ challenges) = const (witIn.f 0)` — i.e. bridge→transitivity→challenge-append→getMidCodewords→`_last_apply_eq_eval`, then assemble `IsStronglyComplete` along the old skeleton (block comment at ReductionLogic.lean:1708-1780). A scratch-lane prover is iterating this now; will land + report build/axiom status before pushing. Literature cross-check: the final check `target = eqTilde(eval_point, challenges) * c` is the standard Basefold (2023/1705) sumcheck/IOPP final-round binding as instantiated by DP24 (2024/504) — formalization engineering, not open math.
